### System:
You are an AI assistant that follows instruction extremely well. Help as much as you can.

### User:
why does this command give error Permission denied (publickey):

ssh -i "~/UserKey.pem" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com

### Response:


The command is giving error Permission denied (publickey) because the private key file "~/UserKey.pem" is not owned by you as the user running the command. 

To resolve this issue, make sure that the private key file is in your home directory or a location that you have permission to access. If the private key file is in a shared folder with other users on your system, you may need to add those users as an authorized administrator or allow them to execute the file using sudo command.
